CHAPTER ______
1 AN ACT concerning
2 Qualifying Nonprofit Organizations – Incarcerated Individual Training and
3 Reentry Grant Fund – Extension
4 FOR the purpose of extending the fiscal years in which the Governor may include a certain
5 appropriation in the annual budget bill for certain qualifying nonprofit organizations
6 that provide certain services to incarcerated or formerly incarcerated individuals;
7 extending the termination date for provisions relating to funding for certain services
8 to incarcerated and formerly incarcerated individuals; and generally relating to
9 reentry services and employment opportunities for formerly incarcerated
10 individuals.
11 BY repealing and reenacting, with amendments,
12 Article – Public Safety
13 Section 4–1013
14 Annotated Code of Maryland
15 (2022 Replacement Volume and 2025 Supplement)
16 BY repealing and reenacting, with amendments,
17 Chapter 892 of the Acts of the General Assembly of 2024
18 Section 2
19 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
20 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
EXPLANATION: CAPITALS INDICATE MATTER ADDED TO EXISTING LAW.
[Brackets] indicate matter deleted from existing law.
