2 SENATE BILL 305
1 Article – Public Safety
2 4–1013.
3 (a) In this section, “qualifying nonprofit organization” means an organization
4 that:
5 (1) provides training and reentry assistance for incarcerated and formerly
6 incarcerated individuals;
7 (2) provides training for at least 50 incarcerated or formerly incarcerated
8 individuals per year in automotive repair;
9 (3) is able to provide an automotive repair certificate from a nationally
10 recognized automotive repair organization to eligible participants; and
11 (4) demonstrates a minimum of a 50% employment placement rate for
12 eligible participants in a paid automotive repair job.
13 (b) For fiscal years 2026 through [2028] 2029, each year the Governor may
14 include in the annual budget bill an appropriation of $1,000,000 to be used solely as an
15 operating grant to qualifying nonprofit organizations for the purpose of providing training
16 to formerly incarcerated individuals in automotive repair.
17 (c) The Governor’s Office of Crime Prevention[, Youth,] and [Victim Services]
18 POLICY shall administer the grant funds to qualifying nonprofit organizations in
19 accordance with § 4–1008 of this subtitle.
20 (d) A qualifying nonprofit organization that receives a grant under this section
21 shall submit for each fiscal year the following to the Executive Director of the Governor’s
22 Office of Crime Prevention[, Youth,] and [Victim Services] POLICY:
23 (1) proof of the expenditure of the grant funds and the purposes for which
24 the funds were expended;
25 (2) the total number of incarcerated and formerly incarcerated individuals
26 who received services; and
27 (3) any related outcome–based performance measures.
28 Chapter 892 of the Acts of 2024
29 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect July
30 1, 2024. It shall remain effective for a period of [4] 5 years and, at the end of [June 30,
31 2028] JUNE 30, 2029, this Act, with no further action required by the General Assembly,
32 shall be abrogated and of no further force and effect.

SENATE BILL 305 3
1 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect July
2 1, 2026.
